moxie

Interface ObjectCheck<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of the mock object on which checks are being carried out.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Cardinality<ObjectCheck<T>>, Check<ObjectCheck<T>,Object>

    public interface ObjectCheck<T>
extends Check<ObjectCheck<T>,Object>, Cardinality<ObjectCheck<T>>
    Interface containing domain-specific language methods called in "the middle bit" of statements that perform post-invocation verifications on mock object instances.

    See documentation on the parent Check interface for a high-level introduction to the syntax.

      • on

        void on(String methodName,
        Object... params)
        Reflectively specify the method on which this check is to be performed.

        Use this method to check invocations of protected or package-private methods which cannot be specified using the no-parameters version of this method because they are inaccessible from your test class.

        Note that on(), when(), get() and got() do exactly the same thing - use whichever method results in the syntax you prefer best.

        Parameters:
        methodName - The name of the method to be checked
        params - Values or MoxieMatchers invocations matching the parameters to be verified
